Contributor<T>
public class ContributorImpl<T>
extends Object
implements Contributor<T>

This class represents default implementation of service contribution definition that distributively configures services. It is based on configuring service by invoking module method.

1.0

supports

public boolean supports(Service service)
Checks if this service contribution definition supports specified service. This contributor supports service if its service identifier or service class correspond to configured ones.

Specified by:
supports in interface Contributor<T>
Parameters:

Returns:
true if this service configuration definition supports specified service, false otherwise

contribute

public void contribute(ServiceResources<T> resources)
Contributes to service configuration using service resource. It manipulates with three types of service configuration: Configuration, OrderedConfiguration and MappedConfiguration and provides collection, list and map to service via ServiceResources respectively. It configures service by invoking configured module method.

Specified by:
contribute in interface Contributor<T>
Parameters:
resources - service resources
